TY  - JOUR
T1  - Nonparametric Estimation of the Cumulative Intensity Function for a Nonhomogeneous Poisson Process
AU  - Leemis, Lawrence M.
Y1  - 1991/07/01
PY  - 1991
DA  - 1991/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.37.7.886
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.37.7.886
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 886
EP  - 900
VL  - 37
IS  - 7
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - A nonparametric technique for estimating the cumulative intensity function of a nonhomogeneous Poisson process from one or more realizations is developed. This technique does not require any arbitrary parameters from the modeler, and the estimated cumulative intensity function can be used to generate a point process for Monte Carlo simulation by inversion. Three examples are given.
AB  - A nonparametric technique for estimating the cumulative intensity function of a nonhomogeneous Poisson process from one or more realizations is developed. This technique does not require any arbitrary parameters from the modeler, and the estimated cumulative intensity function can be used to generate a point process for Monte Carlo simulation by inversion. Three examples are given.
